description: The ruling junta touted the vote – which has been criticized by Western diplomats and the UN rights chief – as a return to democracy. Former civilian leader Aung San Suu Kyi remains in jail.

headline: War in Ukraine: Zelensky travels to Florida to secure Trump's support
description: Four days after unveiling a 'draft agreement' to end the war, the Ukrainian president is due to meet his US counterpart in Florida on Sunday to address outstanding issues and show that Moscow – not Kyiv – remains the obstacle to peace.

headline: Trump, the Apocalypse and King David: A theological reading of the US president
description: Since his first term, the American president has frequently made apocalyptic and messianic references. Some supporters compare him to biblical figures such as King David, appealing particularly to evangelical Christians, who make up about one-fifth of Americans.

description: Many researchers have observed a resurgence of religious commitment among young people in France, often accompanied by a certain rigorism. This renewed spiritual quest is linked both to the anxieties of our era and, at times, a search for identity.

headline: How dining etiquette reveals social divides among young people
description: Choosing a natural wine, slicing comté cheese the 'right' way, opening an oyster: For young people lacking the right social codes, embarrassment at the table is often inevitable.

headline: Mariupol, Ukraine: A model city of 'new Russia'
description: Since 2015, photographer Gabriele Micalizzi has been documenting the Donbas region from the Russian side of the front line, an area where Moscow enforces very strict access conditions for journalists. In November, he secured permission to enter Donetsk Oblast, a region of occupied Ukraine, and traveled to Mariupol, a city destroyed by Russian forces in 2022, which has since been colonized and rebuilt in record time.
